thread.title: Man found dead at National Harbor as CPAC kicks off
thread.title_full: Man found dead at National Harbor as CPAC kicks off | Washington Examiner

author: Alex Pappas, Sean Langille
title: Man found dead at National Harbor as CPAC kicks off
text:
A man is believed to have jumped to his death Thursday from a parking garage at Maryland's National Harbor as conservatives from across the country gathered at the resort for the annual Conservative Political Action Conference.
Officer Tyler Hunter of the Prince George's County Police Department said "at this point we are ruling this death investigation a suicide."
Hunter said Thursday afternoon the person appears to be an employee of a nearby business and does not appear to be affiliated with CPAC.
The garage is a few blocks from the hotel where CPAC is going on. President Trump is expected to deliver a speech to the convention on Friday.
